cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

The paper discusses ensemble methods and deep learning fusion, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses MNIST dataset as a guiding thread, which is a popular dataset in computer vision, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of heterogeneous ensembles, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions achieving a new record in MNIST, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
